<section xml:id="deleting-items-from-browsers" version="5.0" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"
                                                         xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
                                                         xmlns:xl="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" >
  <title>Deleting items from browsers</title>
  <anchor role="helpid" condition="testSpecificationViewContextId" xml:id="deleting-items-from-browsers.testSpecificationViewContextId">Test Case Browser</anchor>
  <anchor role="helpid" condition="testExecViewContextId" xml:id="deleting-items-from-browsers.testExecViewContextId">Test Suite Browser</anchor>
  <anchor role="helpid" condition="guidancerComponentNameBrowserContextId" xml:id="deleting-items-from-browsers.guidancerComponentNameBrowserContextId">Component Name Browser</anchor>
  <orderedlist>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        To delete a Test Case, Test Suite, Test Job or component
        name, select it in the browser.
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Select ”<emphasis>delete</emphasis>” from the
        context-sensitive menu.
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        You can also delete items by pressing
        <emphasis role="input">»DELETE«</emphasis>
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </orderedlist>
  <para role="warning">
    If the item you want to delete is referenced somewhere in
    your test, you must first remove it from the place where it is
    reused before deleting it.
  </para>
</section>